29:55.293 --> 29:58.046
That's something you don't hear too often,
as in ever.

29:58.046 --> 29:59.589
Hmm.

29:59.589 --> 30:03.301
So, uh,
what's with this website thing you're on?

30:04.385 --> 30:05.553
You heard about that?

30:05.553 --> 30:08.473
One of the other widows,
she keeps track of the blogs.

30:08.473 --> 30:10.517
Yeah, well, I've done a lot of reading.

30:10.517 --> 30:12.727
- I can tell you some stuff.
- I don't wanna know.

30:12.727 --> 30:15.313
- There were bombs in those--
- I don't want to know.

30:15.313 --> 30:17.524
I'm just asking questions, okay?

30:17.524 --> 30:20.944
Not out of fear,
not out of disrespect, but because I can.

30:20.944 --> 30:23.196
- This country was founded on dissent.
- Mmm-hmm.

30:23.196 --> 30:25.824
I realize these days,
that's called being unpatriotic...

30:25.824 --> 30:30.286
Oh, I could give a shit
about you being unpatriotic.

30:31.287 --> 30:33.998
Just do me one favor.

30:33.998 --> 30:36.334
What? What do you want me to do?

30:37.919 --> 30:42.090
Don't turn
my husband's death into a hobby.

30:50.515 --> 30:52.642
That's the Deutsche Bank building.

30:52.642 --> 30:54.185
It's still eating firemen.

30:54.185 --> 30:56.521
You know,
we see these people coming and going.

30:56.521 --> 30:58.398
They do this all day, every day.

30:58.398 --> 31:00.608
They don't really give
a shit anymore about it.

31:00.608 --> 31:03.736
And the truth is,
when the Twin Towers were standing,

31:04.612 --> 31:06.239
they looked like shit.

31:06.239 --> 31:07.574
Everybody forgets that now.

31:07.574 --> 31:11.578
They used to have magazine articles every
couple of years about how ugly they were,

31:11.578 --> 31:14.497
how they loomed
over the rest of Manhattan.

31:15.456 --> 31:17.500
Come on,
I'm gonna show you a different view.

31:23.256 --> 31:26.050
Three, and four.

31:26.050 --> 31:28.136
24,400.

31:28.803 --> 31:30.763
And my cut, let's see...

31:32.473 --> 31:33.766
Shit. Uh, hello?

31:33.766 --> 31:35.226
Somebody in there?

31:35.226 --> 31:37.687
Uh, oh, hey, Franc.
Uh, what's going on, man?

31:37.687 --> 31:39.981
I need my keys. What are you doing?

31:39.981 --> 31:41.691
Nothing. I'll be out in a sec.

31:41.691 --> 31:43.818
I'm just, um, I'm jerkin' off.

31:43.818 --> 31:44.986
I...

31:45.862 --> 31:47.113
You're jerkin' off?

31:47.113 --> 31:50.116
Yep. And I'm almost done,
so just hang on one sec.

31:50.909 --> 31:52.035
Oh, yeah.

31:52.035 --> 31:53.870
Seriously, I need my keys right now.

31:53.870 --> 31:55.413
Oh, work it, daddy.

31:56.164 --> 31:57.498
Ooh, yeah. Work it out.

31:57.498 --> 31:58.958
Work it out.

31:58.958 --> 32:00.627
She's gonna blow!

32:08.509 --> 32:10.887
- Hey, bro.
- Hey.

32:10.887 --> 32:12.263
Here's your keys.

32:14.849 --> 32:15.975
Thank you.

32:15.975 --> 32:17.477
Cleanup on aisle five.

32:19.938 --> 32:21.356
This is my business partner.

32:22.482 --> 32:23.733
Great.

32:26.861 --> 32:28.446
Thank you.

32:28.446 --> 32:29.656
Here you go. Enjoy.

32:31.282 --> 32:32.951
Uh, you're drinking?

32:32.951 --> 32:37.455
No. It's a little, uh,
trick I learned from my sponsor.

32:37.455 --> 32:39.540
It's, um... I don't drink it.

32:39.540 --> 32:41.584
I just order a drink, and I let it sit.

32:41.584 --> 32:43.336
Uh, it works, actually.

32:44.337 --> 32:49.384
Just the fumes alone remind me
of a place I don't want to go to.

32:49.384 --> 32:50.468
Mmm.

32:51.344 --> 32:53.388
Are you haunted, Tommy?

32:58.810 --> 33:01.229
What's that supposed to mean?

33:03.272 --> 33:07.443
So, um, how many times have
you been visited by your cousin?

33:09.487 --> 33:10.947
What do you want me to say?

33:12.156 --> 33:13.282
The truth?

33:13.282 --> 33:16.953
You know,
I'm sure you've heard every, uh,

33:18.705 --> 33:22.291
angle from talking to people
in the firehouse about this.

33:22.291 --> 33:25.420
But I'll run it down for you,
what really happened, okay?

33:25.420 --> 33:27.922
Coming down here that day,
everybody knew,

33:29.465 --> 33:34.971
uh, you know,
this was something extraordinary.

33:34.971 --> 33:37.223
It wasn't a normal
run-of-the-mill call, obviously.

33:37.223 --> 33:38.474
I think some of the young guys,

33:38.474 --> 33:40.309
when we got in the lobby
of the first tower,

33:40.309 --> 33:42.228
they probably thought
it was a death sentence.

33:42.228 --> 33:43.688
Not necessarily true.

33:43.688 --> 33:46.149
The older guys like myself,
we were looking at it like,

33:46.149 --> 33:48.568
"This is a big call, but it's a call."

33:48.568 --> 33:51.029
We were sent up. Jimmy started to go.

33:51.029 --> 33:52.447
This lady's purse spilled.

33:52.447 --> 33:54.240
Instinct, I reacted,

33:54.949 --> 33:58.202
one of the other guys picking stuff
up off the floor, helping her.

33:58.202 --> 33:59.287
I was a little late.

33:59.287 --> 34:00.747
I caught up to Jimmy.

34:00.747 --> 34:03.124
We came down, a couple of grabs.

34:03.124 --> 34:04.333
He had two. I had one.

34:04.333 --> 34:08.629
And he was joking with me how, you know,
he was making me look bad again.

34:08.629 --> 34:11.090
We handed them off.

34:11.090 --> 34:14.093
And, uh, you know,
then I kind of lost track of him.

34:14.927 --> 34:18.598
I don't, uh,
really have any regrets.

34:18.598 --> 34:20.224
I don't live my life that way.

34:20.224 --> 34:23.394
I'm not a "shoulda, woulda, coulda"
kind of guy.

34:23.394 --> 34:28.733
And I thought he,
uh, went in the first tower.

34:28.733 --> 34:30.109
And I was okay with that.

34:31.277 --> 34:34.489
Everybody talks about, uh, that day.

34:34.489 --> 34:36.199
Nobody talks about what it was,

34:36.199 --> 34:38.618
which was the single
greatest rescue mission

34:38.618 --> 34:40.536
in the history
of the goddamn fire service.

34:40.536 --> 34:42.622
That's how I look at it.
3,000 people dead.

34:42.622 --> 34:43.748
But you know what?

34:44.707 --> 34:45.792
Shoulda, woulda, coulda.

34:45.792 --> 34:47.627
Think about the numbers
that would have been

34:47.627 --> 34:51.047
if we hadn't have done the job we did
that day. I was fine with it.

34:51.631 --> 34:54.842
When you came up
with this footage and this idea,

34:55.468 --> 34:59.180
this proof that he actually
went into the second tower...

35:00.932 --> 35:03.476
That's a little different.
That's, you know...

35:05.103 --> 35:10.316
If I had known, you know, where he was,
I could have gone in.

35:10.316 --> 35:13.778
Maybe I would have been able to grab him.

35:13.778 --> 35:16.572
You know, if we had
an extra 45 minutes that day,

35:16.572 --> 35:19.117
I think we could have gotten
everybody out.

35:19.117 --> 35:21.369
So it just makes me, you know...

35:25.331 --> 35:30.044
Either I could have gotten him out,
or we both would have been in there.

35:30.044 --> 35:31.295
Whatever.

35:32.797 --> 35:34.006
Either way, you know...

35:36.717 --> 35:39.137
We would be together, uh, right now.

35:39.137 --> 35:40.638
You know?

35:40.638 --> 35:44.684
Sometimes, uh,
when I'm falling asleep at night,

35:44.684 --> 35:48.271
I have this weird thing.

35:48.271 --> 35:52.775
I think I'm him,
and I'm inside the first tower,

35:52.775 --> 35:55.319
and it's coming down on top of me,

35:55.319 --> 35:58.573
and it's like the last few seconds,
and then it goes black.

35:58.573 --> 36:01.826
I think it's a normal thing
for people who lose somebody

36:01.826 --> 36:03.202
in an accident of any kind,

36:03.202 --> 36:05.621
is just wondering
what the last few seconds were like.

36:07.874 --> 36:12.044
My wife, uh,
says that makes me a narcissist.

36:14.380 --> 36:17.049
This coming from a woman who can't walk by

36:17.049 --> 36:20.094
a storefront window
without looking at her own ass.

36:22.054 --> 36:23.222
Whatever.

36:26.058 --> 36:30.062
What if you never see him again?

36:36.485 --> 36:37.695
Yeah.

36:46.787 --> 36:48.122
Let's go.

36:50.082 --> 36:51.292
Um...

37:11.395 --> 37:14.148
It's tough, dude.
They told me I gotta cut my hair off.

37:14.148 --> 37:16.150
All the guys in my class
are bigger than me,

37:16.150 --> 37:18.486
they can press more than me,
carry more gear.

37:18.486 --> 37:20.863
Hey, no worries.
You just gotta bulk up.

37:20.863 --> 37:24.575
I got this killer protein shake
that kicks ass for packing on the lbs.

37:24.575 --> 37:26.619
